Open Putty:

  - In the Category pane, select Session, and complete the following fields:
    a. In Host Name, enter ec2-user@public_dns_name.
    b. Port, 22.
    c. Connection type: SSH
  
  - In the Category pane, expand Connection, expand SSH, and then select Auth. Complete the following:
    a. Click Browse.
    b. Select the KeyDevOps.ppk file that you downloaded, and then click Open.
    c. Click Open to start the PuTTY session
  
  - Use the ssh command to connect to the instance. 
  - ssh -i "private key(.pem)" ec2-user@public_dns_name.
  - Run command
    a. sudo yum update â€“y
